	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Well I'd like to add my experience to the rogue thing here. As far as melee classes to, you have 2 main 'relevant to melee' attributes, one is AC(taking damage)and the other is STR(giving damage). Now what defines a 'tank', I'll tell you, one little skill, 'taunt'...if you have taunt, you're a tank(accourding to verant)if you do not have taunt, then you are not 'subjectivly' [supposed] to get hit. Now, as a rogue, what you will find yourself doing, or rather, you most indearing and relevant ability, from when you get it at 10, to 60. Is Backstab. Nothing else really matters. Backstab is what sets the rogue appart from all the other classes. Now, as far as damage goes, accourding to verant once agian, the most relevant stat, effecting damage output by a character is your str. It will directly control your MAX damage(depending on your lvl, 1-9 max damage is 21, 10-19 is 33ish, depending on your STR, I've seen the str bunus as early as lvl 9, when my weapon damage was 6(damage per weapon is calculated (weapon damage X 2 + 1=total damage. Meaning if you have a 6 damage weapon, you'll max hit for 12, sometimes 13, at least as far as lower lvls go. But with 232STR at lvl 9, I did hit for 14. but after you increase in lvl you get 'bonus' damage because of your lvl 'bonus' damage because of your STR, and 'bonus' damage depending on your weapons 'delay'(this added in patchs making weapons with low del get less bonus, and weapons with 40+del get more damage bonus) But, knowing how important 'DEALING' out damage is for a rogue(being your most important ability at higher lvl's) and knowing facts such as(info released from verant directly) your AGL assist in being missed, 'dodging, parry' that sort of thing...and also understanding that you simply cannot 'backstab' while facing something, isn't it really irrelivent what your AGL is, as a rogue, you're not a tank, and you don't have many hps, coupled with the fact that to BS you have to be behind something, then 'dodging,parry,getting missed'...well, is NOT important, you don't wanna get hit anway, so AGL is irellevant. I chose the Barbarian, the highest str for rogue, and as the guise of the deciver(now changed to 'mask of deception' is bard/rogue only' you can be a DE at lvl 16(when the item is usable) so I get HUGE str, and in a little (can see in the dark PERFECTLY) de rogue. Now, to give examples, at lvl 10, when rogues get backstab, I had saved up all my training points, and with a 6 damage weapon, could BS for a max of 47 I believe(STR at the time was I think 150) now, being lvl 23, and with a 10 damage peircing weapon, I can BS for 118. I do BS for around 100 quite often, and my damage from weilding 2 10 damage weapons range in the mid 20's, highest hit for 28. STR controls MAX damage, in addition to 'average' damage. I promise you, go ALL str and you will be SOO happy, my rogue now has 188 str and is an INSANE damage dealer, just to give an example, at lvl 18, I KS'ed(on accident, didn't realise how much damage I was doing) lockjaw from a 27 paly. From the BS's I was doing, and adding the rogue 'evade' ability, I NEVER got hit by LJ one time and put out horrible ammounts of damage. DEX(info from post on message boards from verant) controls weapon proc chance, weapon skill increase) NOT chance to hit. And one thing I've learned, if you are useing a weapon, SOLY based on what it procs, you may have made a gravely horrible desition. Proc is nice, but don't expect it to ALWAYS save your hide. I've found through many observations, that good old dam/del does more than any proc over time. Having played 3 warriors to lvl 20(testing all starting points into STR for one, DEX for one, and AGL for the other) STR had the most bunus effect in melee, played ranger to 25, SK to 40, mage to 21, druid to 25, and my 23 rogue. I have grouped with other rogue about my lvl, and with my str bonus I can outdamage even the tanks VERY easily. I'm workin on getting her STR as close to 255 as possible, will be happy with 200. But in melee, using 'evade' nothing attacks me anyway, so all and I mean, ALL about damage output. I played a woodelf rogue to 17, dumped half starting points into dex, the other into agl, BIG mistake. At lvl 17, I would BS for 41, Max, and with the same weapon, my barb, with her super STR did 46ish at 10...saaaad...but it showed me just how important STR is to the melee, so if you're the tank AC first, STR second, as the rogue, dump all str, and secondary to that will be STA, because all the insane swinging you will be doing at higher lvls quad attacking, will kill your sta, so all str, then whatever you have left over put that into sta. At mid higher lvls, you'll be with a cleric, or shammy or a buff class, so, if you want ac, or hps, get a buff, but all str will make you a straigt up, killing machine....trust me. If you want to flame me, names Pacification Process. <BR>
<BR>
Pacification Process complete, Target has been pacified.<BR>
<BR>
ps:at lvl 23, my ATK, is almost 600(for comparison, my 40SK's ATK little over 800. his str is 129)<BR>
 
				</font>
			</td>

